Already a subscriber, but don't have a login?

Activate your digital access.Are you bored? Check out these community events.CONNECTTWEETLINKEDINCOMMENTEMAILMORE

Monday

Adult book club, 6 p.m., Paxton Branch Library, 113 Dewey St., Bainbridge.

Craft time: Bottle bottom turtles, 6 p.m., Kingston Branch Library, 17 Main St., Kingston.

Button making, 6:30 p.m., Huntington Branch Library, 188 Huntsman Road, Chillicothe. Teens and preteens can design their own or choose from a design.

Calling all board gamers, 6 p.m., Main Library, 140 S. Paint St., Chillicothe. This month's featured games are "Fluxx" and "Smash Up".

Euchre club, 5 p.m., Paxton Branch Library, 113 Dewey St., Bainbridge. Partners will be picked at the time of the event. Cards will be provided.

Harry Potter read-aloud, 3:30 p.m., Mt. Logan Branch Library, 841 E. Main St., Chillicothe.

Read to the listening dog, 3-5 p.m., Northside Branch Library, 550 Buckeye St., Chillicothe. Call the library to reserve your 15-minute time slot.

Story time, 6:30 p.m., Richmond Dale Public Library Branch, 770 Main St., Richmond Dale.

Stories and fun, 10:30 a.m., Northside Branch Library, 550 Buckeye St., Chillicothe. Start your morning off right with your little "wiggle worms".There will be music, movement, baby signs and stories for children up to 3 years old.

Tuesday

Beginner's Quilting, 4 p.m., Paxton (Bainbridge) Branch Library, 204 North Quarry St., Bainbridge.

Diabetes Talk, noon, Main Library Annex, 146 S. Paint St., Chillicothe. Come and meet Adena Endocrinologist Gianina L. Usera, MD, ECNU. Dr. Usera will talk about what it means to have diabetes, ways to try and prevent it, ways to manage it, and the role of nutrition in its management.

Hopewell Culture Park visits the library, 4:30 p.m., Howard S. Young (Frankfort) Branch Library, 167 Springfield St., Frankfort. Visit with a ranger from the Hopewell Culture National Historic Park. Learn about the 2,000 year history of this incredible park. You may also participate in an archeology dig.

Open gym basketball, 8-9:30 p.m., Mount Logan Elementary School, 841 E. Main St., Chillicothe.

Sips and succulents, 6 p.m., The Cozy Inn, 339 Western Ave., Chillicothe. Create your very own terrarium. All supplies will be provided.

Talk like a pirate day, 4-7:30 p.m., Huntington Branch Library, 188 Huntsman Road, Chillicothe. Make a pirate hat, create an origami parrot, and talk like a pirate.

Troll bogey slime shenanigans, 4 p.m., Mount Logan Branch Library, 841 E. Main St., Chillicothe. Listen to Harry Potter and make slime. To make reservations, visit www.crcpl.org.

Wednesday

Brown bag book chat, noon, Main Library, 140 S. Paint St., Chillicothe. Bring a lunch, and come chat about "White Dog Fell from the Sky" by Eleanor Morse. To make reservations, call www.crcpl.org.

Lego fun, 4 p.m., South Salem Branch Library, 4297 Broadway St., South Salem.

Metro Five-0: Level 4 Backcountry Pond Study, 10 a.m., Clear Creek Metro Park, 185 Clear Creek Road, Rockbridge. This is a rugged 4-mile hike for those 50 years old and older.

Preschool stories and crafts, 1:30 p.m., Northside Branch Library, 550 Buckeye St., Chillicothe. Listen to stories and make a craft.

Quilters Circle, 4 p.m., Huntington Branch Library, 188 Huntsman Road, Chillicothe. Creating your own quilt in a group setting.

Storytime, 1 p.m., Kingston Branch Library, 17 Main St., Kingston. Preschoolers will listen to a story and make a craft.

Thursday

The social hour (for teens), 3:30-4:30 p.m., Main Library, 140 S. Paint St., Chillicothe. There will be crafts, snacks and games for children 12 to 18 years old. To register, call www.crcpl.org.
